### Step 1 — `backend/src/modules/analytics/analytics.service.ts`

**Add `deleteDefinition` and `listSchedules` functions, then expose them on the exported object.**

Location: after the `updateDefinition` function (around line 152), add:

```
async function deleteDefinition(id: string, actorId?: string) {
  // Soft-delete: set isActive = false
  const existing = await prisma.reportDefinition.findUnique({ where: { id } });
  if (!existing) throw new NotFoundError('Report definition not found');

  const definition = await prisma.reportDefinition.update({
    where: { id },
    data: { isActive: false },
  });

  logger.info({ definitionId: id, actorId }, 'Report definition soft-deleted');
  return definition;
}

async function listSchedules(query: { page?: number; pageSize?: number }) {
  // Returns definitions that are scheduled (frequency != ON_DEMAND)
  const { skip, take, page, pageSize } = parsePagination(query);

  const [definitions, total] = await Promise.all([
    prisma.reportDefinition.findMany({
      where: { isActive: true, frequency: { not: 'ON_DEMAND' } },
      skip,
      take,
      orderBy: { createdAt: 'desc' },
      include: { _count: { select: { reports: true } } },
    }),
    prisma.reportDefinition.count({ where: { isActive: true, frequency: { not: 'ON_DEMAND' } } }),
  ]);

  return { data: definitions, meta: buildMeta(total, page, pageSize) };
}
```

Then update the exported object at line 1031 to add `deleteDefinition` and `listSchedules`.

The `listSchedules` function reuses `parsePagination` / `buildMeta` already imported. No new imports needed.

